commands.name: ACTIVATE_SCRIPTED_CAMS

commands.short_desc: Adds the specified vehicle to the mission deletion list (to be deleted after the mission is finished)

commands.name: ADD_CHAR_DECISION_MAKER_EVENT_RESPONSE
commands.short_desc: Sets which action should occur according to the event on the following parameters

commands.name: ADD_COVER_BLOCKING_AREA
commands.short_desc: Adds a cover blocking area

commands.name: ADD_COVER_POINT
commands.short_desc: Adds a cover point to a cover object

commands.name: ADD_EXPLOSION
commands.short_desc: Creates an explosion with given parameters. Do NOT over use. It will stop rendering the explosion graphics/camera shake

commands.name: ADD_GROUP_TO_NETWORK_RESTART_NODE_GROUP_LIST
commands.short_desc: Adds a group to the network restart node group list

commands.name: ADD_HOSPITAL_RESTART
commands.short_desc: Adds a hospital spawn point when the player dies

commands.name: ADD_LINE_TO_CONVERSATION
commands.short_desc: Adds a line to a conversation

commands.name: ADD_LINE_TO_MOBILE_PHONE_CALL
commands.short_desc: Adds a line to a mobile phone call

commands.name: ADD_LINE_TO_SCRIPTED_CONVERSATION
commands.short_desc: Adds a line to a scripted conversation

commands.name: ADD_NAVMESH_REQUIRED_REGION
commands.short_desc: Adds a navmesh to a required region

commands.name: ADD_NEEDED_AT_POSN
commands.short_desc: Adds a position that the player is needed at (used a lot on dating)

commands.name: ADD_NETWORK_RESTART
commands.short_desc: Adds a point to spawn at once the player dies on a network game

commands.name: ADD_NEW_CONVERSATION_SPEAKER
commands.short_desc: Adds a new conversation speaker

commands.name: ADD_NEW_FRONTEND_CONVERSATION_SPEAKER
commands.short_desc: Adds a new frontend conversation speaker

commands.name: ADD_NEXT_MESSAGE_TO_PREVIOUS_BRIEFS
commands.short_desc: Determines whether the next message shown will be shown in the previous briefs

commands.name: ADD_OBJECT_TO_INTERIOR_ROOM_BY_KEY
commands.short_desc: Adds an object to the interior room denoted by the key

commands.name: ADD_OBJECT_TO_INTERIOR_ROOM_BY_NAME
commands.short_desc: Adds an object to the interior room denoted by its name

commands.name: ADD_PED_TO_CINEMATOGRAPHY_AI
commands.short_desc: Adds a ped to a cinematography AI object

commands.name: ADD_PED_TO_MISSION_DELETION_LIST
commands.short_desc: Adds a ped to the mission deletion list

commands.name: ADD_PICKUP_TO_INTERIOR_ROOM_BY_KEY
commands.short_desc: Adds a pickup to the interior room denoted by the key

commands.name: ADD_PICKUP_TO_INTERIOR_ROOM_BY_NAME
commands.short_desc: Adds a pickup to the interior room denoted by its name

commands.name: ADD_POINT_TO_GPS_RACE_TRACK
commands.short_desc: Adds a point to the GPS Race Track

commands.name: ADD_POLICE_RESTART
commands.short_desc: Adds a police station spawn point when the player gets busted

commands.name: ADD_SCENARIO_BLOCKING_AREA
commands.short_desc: Dictates the area you can go in while a scenario is in operation

commands.name: ADD_SCORE
commands.short_desc: Adds money to the player

commands.name: ADD_SIMPLE_BLIP_FOR_PICKUP
commands.short_desc: Adds a simple blip on the map corresponding to the pickups position

commands.name: ADD_SPAWN_BLOCKING_AREA
commands.short_desc: Adds an area where players can't spawn

commands.name: ADD_SPHERE
commands.short_desc: Creates a sphere

commands.name: ADD_STRING_TO_NEWS_SCROLLBAR
commands.short_desc: Adds a string to the news scrollbar as seen in The Triangle, south of Star Junction. It can be completely cleared by calling the function CLEAR_NEWS_SCROLLBAR. The news scrollbar in northern Star Junction is controlled by scrollbars.dat. If you use again without clearing it, the string will be added next to the previous one that was created

commands.name: ADD_STUCK_CAR_CHECK
commands.short_desc: Adds a check for a stuck car (controlled by the AI). To check if the vehicle is stuck use IS_CAR_STUCK. TO remove the stuck check use REMOVE_STUCK_CAR_CHECK

commands.name: ADD_STUCK_CAR_CHECK_WITH_WARP
commands.short_desc: Adds a check similar to ADD_STUCK_CAR_CHECK with several flags to put the vehicle back to the path if its stuck or flipped. To check if the vehicle is stuck use IS_CAR_STUCK. To remove the stuck check use REMOVE_STUCK_CAR_CHECK

commands.name: ADD_STUNT_JUMP
commands.short_desc: Adds a stunt jump

commands.name: ADD_TO_HTML_SCRIPT_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Adds a string to the HTML script object

commands.name: ADD_TO_PREVIOUS_BRIEF
commands.short_desc: Adds some text to the previous brief

commands.name: ADD_TO_PREVIOUS_BRIEF_WITH_UNDERSCORE
commands.short_desc: Adds text to the previous brief with an underscore

commands.name: ADD_UPSIDEDOWN_CAR_CHECK
commands.short_desc: Adds an upside down check to a vehicle

commands.name: ALLOCATE_SCRIPT_TO_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Allocates a script to an object, which will be activated when the player is within the specified area around it

commands.name: ALLOCATE_SCRIPT_TO_RANDOM_PED
commands.short_desc: Allocates a script to a random ped activating when the player is within the specified area around it

commands.name: ALLOW_AUTO_CONVERSATION_LOOKATS
commands.short_desc: Allows a character to automatically look at other characters in the conversation when they are talking

commands.name: ALLOW_EMERGENCY_SERVICES
commands.short_desc: Switches the emergency services on and off

commands.name: ALLOW_GAME_TO_PAUSE_FOR_STREAMING
commands.short_desc: Allows the game to pause for streaming, or switches the function off

commands.name: ALLOW_GANG_RELATIONSHIPS_TO_BE_CHANGED_BY_NEXT_COMMAND
commands.short_desc: Allows the gang relationships to be changed by the next command

commands.name: ALLOW_LOCKON_TO_FRIENDLY_PLAYERS
commands.short_desc: Allows locking on to friendly players

commands.name: ALLOW_LOCKON_TO_RANDOM_PEDS
commands.short_desc: Allows locking on to random peds

commands.name: ALLOW_MULTIPLE_DRIVEBY_PICKUPS
commands.short_desc: Allows multiple driveby pickups

commands.name: ALLOW_NETWORK_POPULATION_GROUP_CYCLING
commands.short_desc: Allows network population group cycling

commands.name: ALLOW_ONE_TIME_ONLY_COMMANDS_TO_RUN
commands.short_desc: Determines whether one time only commands are allowed to be run

commands.name: ALLOW_PLAYER_TO_CARRY_NON_MISSION_OBJECTS
commands.short_desc: Allows the player to pickup small random litter. If set to 0, the player can't pick up objects. Objects already in Niko's hand will still be held on

commands.name: ALLOW_REACTION_ANIMS
commands.short_desc: Allows reaction animations on a character

commands.name: ALLOW_STUNT_JUMPS_TO_TRIGGER
commands.short_desc: Allows stunt jumps to trigger

commands.name: ALLOW_TARGET_WHEN_INJURED
commands.short_desc: Allows targeting on the character when injured

commands.name: ALLOW_THIS_SCRIPT_TO_BE_PAUSED
commands.short_desc: Allows the script is executed in to be paused.For example, when entering the Custom Match menu, every pausable script gets paused

commands.name: ALTER_WANTED_LEVEL
commands.short_desc: Alters the player's wanted level. Sometimes the wanted level doesn't change immediately. Include APPLY_WANTED_LEVEL_CHANGE_NOW to immediately change the wanted level

commands.name: ALTER_WANTED_LEVEL_NO_DROP
commands.short_desc: Increments a players wanted level

commands.name: ALWAYS_USE_HEAD_ON_HORN_ANIM_WHEN_DEAD_IN_CAR
commands.short_desc: Turns on/off the need to always use the head on horn animation when dead in a car

commands.name: AMBIENT_AUDIO_BANK_NO_LONGER_NEEDED
commands.short_desc: Makes the ambient audio bank no longer needed

commands.name: ANCHOR_BOAT
commands.short_desc: Anchors or lets loose a boat

commands.name: ANCHOR_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Anchors or lets loose an object

commands.name: APPLY_FORCE_TO_CAR
commands.short_desc: Applies force to a car. Param 10 specifies if the force direction is relative to direction object is facing (true), or static world direction (false)

commands.name: APPLY_FORCE_TO_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Applies force to an object. Param 10 specifies if the force direction is relative to direction object is facing (true), or static world direction (false)

commands.name: APPLY_FORCE_TO_PED
commands.short_desc: Applies force to an ped. Params 6,7,8 does not seem to work in animated or ragdolled state. Param 10 specifies if the force direction is relative to direction object is facing (true), or static world direction (false)

commands.name: APPLY_WANTED_LEVEL_CHANGE_NOW
commands.short_desc: Applies the wanted level changes immediately

commands.name: ARE_ALL_NAVMESH_REGIONS_LOADED
commands.short_desc: Returns true or false depending if all the navmesh regions are loaded

commands.name: ARE_ANY_CHARS_NEAR_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Checks if there are any characters in a defined radius around a defined character

commands.name: ARE_CREDITS_FINISHED
commands.short_desc: Checks whether the credits are finished rolling

commands.name: ARE_ENEMY_PEDS_IN_AREA
commands.short_desc: Checks whether there are any enemy peds in the area

commands.name: ARE_TAXI_LIGHTS_ON
commands.short_desc: Returns true or false depending on whether the taxi lights are on

commands.name: ARE_WIDESCREEN_BORDERS_ACTIVE
commands.short_desc: Determines whether the widescreen borders are active

commands.name: ASCII_INT_TO_STRING
commands.short_desc: Converts an integer to a string

commands.name: ATAN
commands.short_desc: Performs an atan2 function on the y and x numbers provided

commands.name: ATAN2
commands.short_desc: Performs an atan2 function on the y and x numbers provided

commands.name: ATTACH_ANIMS_TO_MODEL
commands.short_desc: Attaches animations to a model

commands.name: ATTACH_CAM_TO_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Attaches a camera to an object

commands.name: ATTACH_CAM_TO_PED
commands.short_desc: Attaches a camera to a pedestrian

commands.name: ATTACH_CAM_TO_VEHICLE
commands.short_desc: Attaches a camera to a vehicle

commands.name: ATTACH_CAM_TO_VIEWPORT
commands.short_desc: Attaches a camera to a viewport

commands.name: ATTACH_CAR_TO_CAR
commands.short_desc: Attaches two Vehicles together. Rotation are in radians. If the 'Absolute offsets' boolean is true the offsets are absolute (to the world) otherwise they are relative (to the vehicle)

commands.name: ATTACH_CAR_TO_CAR_PHYSICALLY
commands.short_desc: Attaches a Vehicle to another Vehicle Physically

commands.name: ATTACH_CAR_TO_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Attaches a vehicle to an object

commands.name: ATTACH_CAR_TO_OBJECT_PHYSICALLY
commands.short_desc: Attaches a Vehicle to an Object Physically

commands.name: ATTACH_OBJECT_TO_CAR
commands.short_desc: Attaches an object to a car

commands.name: ATTACH_OBJECT_TO_CAR_PHYSICALLY
commands.short_desc: Attaches an Object to a Vehicle Physically

commands.name: ATTACH_OBJECT_TO_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Attaches 2 Objects together

commands.name: ATTACH_OBJECT_TO_OBJECT_PHYSICALLY
commands.short_desc: Attaches an Object to another Object Physically

commands.name: ATTACH_OBJECT_TO_PED
commands.short_desc: Attaches an object to the ped

commands.name: ATTACH_PED_TO_CAR
commands.short_desc: Attaches a ped to a vehicle

commands.name: ATTACH_PED_TO_CAR_PHYSICALLY
commands.short_desc: Attaches a Ped to a Vehicle physically

commands.name: ATTACH_PED_TO_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Attaches a Ped to an Object

commands.name: ATTACH_PED_TO_OBJECT_PHYSICALLY
commands.short_desc: Attaches a Ped to an Object Physically

commands.name: ATTACH_PED_TO_SHIMMY_EDGE
commands.short_desc: Attaches a Ped to the Shimmy Edge

commands.name: ATTACH_PED_TO_WORLD_PHYSICALLY
commands.short_desc: Attaches a Ped to the World Physically

commands.name: AWARD_ACHIEVEMENT
commands.short_desc: Awards specified achievement to current player. Use HAS_ACHIEVEMENT_BEEN_PASSED to check if the achievement has been passed

commands.name: AWARD_PLAYER_MISSION_RESPECT
commands.short_desc: Awards the player some mission respect statistics

commands.name: BEGIN_CAM_COMMANDS
commands.short_desc: Begins the transaction of camera commands

commands.name: BEGIN_CHAR_SEARCH_CRITERIA
commands.short_desc: Begins the transmission of Character search criteria

commands.name: BEGIN_PED_QUEUE_MEMBERSHIP_LIST
commands.short_desc: Begins the transmission of a Ped queue membership list

commands.name: BLEND_FROM_NM_WITH_ANIM
commands.short_desc: Blends from NM with an Animation

commands.name: BLEND_OUT_CHAR_MOVE_ANIMS
commands.short_desc: Blends out the Characters move Animations

commands.name: BLOCK_CHAR_AMBIENT_ANIMS
commands.short_desc: Blocks a Characters Ambient Animations

commands.name: BLOCK_CHAR_GESTURE_ANIMS
commands.short_desc: Blocks a characters gesture animations

commands.name: BLOCK_CHAR_HEAD_IK
commands.short_desc: Blocks a characters head from animations

commands.name: BLOCK_CHAR_VISEME_ANIMS
commands.short_desc: Blocks a Characters Viseme (facial expression) Animations

commands.name: BLOCK_COWERING_IN_COVER
commands.short_desc: Blocks a Character from cowering in cover

commands.name: BLOCK_PED_WEAPON_SWITCHING
commands.short_desc: Blocks a ped from weapon switching

commands.name: BLOCK_PEEKING_IN_COVER
commands.short_desc: Blocks a Character from Peeking in cover

commands.name: BREAK_CAR_DOOR
commands.short_desc: Breaks or repairs a car door

commands.name: BURST_CAR_TYRE
commands.short_desc: Deflates a vehicle's tire. The tire still stays intact. A crude drawing below shows which ID belongs to which wheel

commands.name: CAM_IS_SPHERE_VISIBLE
commands.short_desc: Checks if the specified camera has a clear line-of-sight towards the specified sphere.Environment (walls, buildings, ground) blocks the line of sight. Because the function has not been fully tested it is not known if objects, peds and vehicles block the line of sight

commands.name: CELL_CAM_ACTIVATE
commands.short_desc: Activates the first person view used when the Camera feature of the cell phone is selected. The player will not be able to move and can only look around. Environmental events like getting hit by a car while is on will return the camera back to third person but the player will still be not able to move

commands.name: CHANGE_BLIP_COLOUR
commands.short_desc: Recolors the blip in the first parameter with the color in the second parameter

commands.name: CHANGE_BLIP_DISPLAY
commands.short_desc: Changes how a blip is displayed in the radar, the map and the world

commands.name: CHANGE_BLIP_NAME_FROM_ASCII
commands.short_desc: Changes blip's name which is displayed while covering it with cursor on the map

commands.name: CHANGE_BLIP_SCALE
commands.short_desc: Changes blip's scale (1.0 = default size)

commands.name: CHANGE_BLIP_SPRITE
commands.short_desc: Changes the blip sprite

commands.name: CHANGE_CAR_COLOUR
commands.short_desc: Changes the colors of the specified vehicle

commands.name: CHANGE_PLAYER_MODEL
commands.short_desc: Changes the Players Model

commands.name: CLEAR_AREA
commands.short_desc: Clears the specified radius of cars

commands.name: CLEAR_AREA_OF_CARS
commands.short_desc: Clears the specified radius of cars

commands.name: CLEAR_AREA_OF_CHARS
commands.short_desc: Clears the specified radius out of chars

commands.name: CLEAR_AREA_OF_COPS
commands.short_desc: Clears the specified radius out of cops

commands.name: CLEAR_AREA_OF_OBJECTS
commands.short_desc: Clears the specified radius out of objects

commands.name: CLEAR_PLAYER_HAS_DAMAGED_AT_LEAST_ONE_PED
commands.short_desc: Clears the last ped damaged for the specific Player

commands.name: CLEAR_PLAYER_HAS_DAMAGED_AT_LEAST_ONE_VEHICLE
commands.short_desc: Clears the last vehicle damaged for the specific player

commands.name: CONVERT_INT_TO_PLAYERINDEX
commands.short_desc: Returns the Player Index from the Player ID. Use GET_PLAYER_ID to get the current player's ID

commands.name: CREATE_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Creates a new character inside the specified vehicle

commands.name: CREATE_CHAR_INSIDE_CAR
commands.short_desc: Creates a new character inside the specified vehicle

commands.name: CREATE_PLAYER
commands.short_desc: Creates a Player

commands.name: DETACH_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Detaches the object from its host

commands.name: DID_SAVE_COMPLETE_SUCCESSFULLY
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the game was saved successfully after the last time the save menu was opened. Returns false if saving failed or if the save menu was cancelled

commands.name: DISABLE_DEBUG_CAM_AND_PLAYER_WARPING
commands.short_desc: Disables the effect of ENABLE_DEBUG_CAM (true); meaning disables the debug cam and double-click player teleporting

commands.name: DISABLE_FRONTEND_RADIO
commands.short_desc: Disables the main vehicle radio. The radio will fade out instead of instantly turning off. Other radio sources like background music or the faint radio heard outside of the vehicle will still be heard. The radio can be reenabled using ENABLE_FRONTEND_RADIO

commands.name: DISABLE_GPS
commands.short_desc: Sets if the GPS should be disabled or not

commands.name: DISABLE_PAUSE_MENU
commands.short_desc: Sets if the pause menu is disabled or not

commands.name: DISABLE_PLAYER_LOCKON
commands.short_desc: Sets if the player can lock on

commands.name: DISABLE_PLAYER_SPRINT
commands.short_desc: Sets if the player can sprint or not

commands.name: DISABLE_POLICE_SCANNER
commands.short_desc: Disables the police scanner, which is the voice heard when the player commits a crime and the police notices it. The police scanner can be reenabled using ENABLE_POLICE_SCANNER

commands.name: DISPLAY_AMMO
commands.short_desc: Toggles display of player's ammo values for the currently selected weapon

commands.name: DISPLAY_AREA_NAME
commands.short_desc: Toggles display of area/zone name (i.e. "Express Way" / "Algonquin" in Ascot Gray and Forest Green on the bottom right)

commands.name: DISPLAY_CASH
commands.short_desc: Toggles display of player's cash value and cash additives (when cash is added/removed)

commands.name: DISPLAY_HUD
commands.short_desc: Toggles HUD

commands.name: DISPLAY_PLAYER_NAMES
commands.short_desc: Displays players' names if the parameter set to true. It removes only names but not circles above players' heads

commands.name: DISPLAY_RADAR
commands.short_desc: Toggles Radar

commands.name: DISPLAY_SNIPER_SCOPE_THIS_FRAME
commands.short_desc: Displays sniper scope for the current frame

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT
commands.short_desc: Draws GXT entry text

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT_WITH_2_NUMBERS
commands.short_desc: Draws a GXT entry text with two additional integer numbers

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT_WITH_3_NUMBERS
commands.short_desc: Draws a GXT entry text with three additional integer numbers

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT_WITH_FLOAT
commands.short_desc: Draws a float number on the screen

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT_WITH_LITERAL_STRING
commands.short_desc: Draws gxt entry with the literal string (4th parameter) at coordinates x, y."~e~" in the gxt text will be replaced with the string. Use "STRING" or ("PZ_STRING") gxt entry (which is just "~e~") to just display the literal string

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT_WITH_NUMBER
commands.short_desc: Draws a GXT entry text with an additional integer number

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT_WITH_STRING
commands.short_desc: Draws a GXT entry text with an additional string

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT_WITH_TWO_LITERAL_STRINGS
commands.short_desc: Draws a GXT entry text with two additional strings

commands.name: DISPLAY_TEXT_WITH_TWO_STRINGS
commands.short_desc: Draws a GXT entry text with two additional non-literal strings

commands.name: DO_SCREEN_FADE_IN
commands.short_desc: Fades in the screen and turns on the sound of the game. Can be called only after DO_SCREEN_FADE_OUT

commands.name: DO_SCREEN_FADE_OUT
commands.short_desc: Fades out the screen and turns off the sound of the game. To fade in the screen and turn on the sound call DO_SCREEN_FADE_IN

commands.name: DOES_BLIP_EXIST
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating if the specified blip handle is allocated in the game

commands.name: DOES_CAM_EXIST
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating if the specified camera handle is allocated in the game

commands.name: DOES_OBJECT_EXIST
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating if the specified object handle is allocated in the game

commands.name: DOES_VEHICLE_EXIST
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating if the specified vehicle handle is allocated in the game

commands.name: DRAW_CHECKPOINT
commands.short_desc: Draws a checkpoint at the specified coordinates, with the specified radius, with the specified color (RGB). Must be used in a loop

commands.name: DRAW_CHECKPOINT_WITH_ALPHA
commands.short_desc: Draws a checkpoint same as DRAW_CHECKPOINT but has an alpha value also for the color

commands.name: DRAW_COLOURED_CYLINDER
commands.short_desc: Creates a translucent, colored arrow at a point. The function has to be in a loop in order for the arrow to appear

commands.name: DRAW_CORONA
commands.short_desc: Creates a corona. The function should be used in a loop

commands.name: DRAW_RECT
commands.short_desc: Draws a rectangle on the screen. The function has to be in a loop in order for the rectangle to appear

commands.name: DRAW_SPRITE
commands.short_desc: Draws sprite which can be get by using GET_TEXTURE or GET_TEXTURE_FROM_STREAMED_TXD

commands.name: DROP_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Makes the ped drop an object they are holding

commands.name: ENABLE_DEBUG_CAM
commands.short_desc: Enables a hidden debug camera that can be controlled with mouse

commands.name: ENABLE_MAX_AMMO_CAP
commands.short_desc: Sets a cap on the amount of ammo the player can carry. Turning on will remove the extra ammo if the player has more ammo than the cap. The caps are set in the Weaponinfo.xml file

commands.name: ENABLE_SHADOWS
commands.short_desc: Enables shadows that are cast by lighting other than the sun. It has the same effect as turning the "Shadow Quality" graphics option off but with the sun still casting shadows. Has no effect when shadows options are turned off

commands.name: EXP
commands.short_desc: Explodes the specified vehicle with an explosion or not

commands.name: EXPLODE_CAR
commands.short_desc: Explodes the specified vehicle with an explosion or not

commands.name: FIND_STREET_NAME_AT_POSITION
commands.short_desc: Returns two hashes for the street you are on (parameters 4 and 5). To convert the hashes to strings, use the GET_STRING_FROM_HASH_KEY native

commands.name: FIRE_SINGLE_BULLET
commands.short_desc: Creates an Invisible Bullet

commands.name: FIX_CAR
commands.short_desc: Repairs the specified vehicle

commands.name: FORCE_CAR_LIGHTS
commands.short_desc: Forces a car's headlights and tail lights to turn on or off. High beams and other lights aren't affected

commands.name: FORCE_LOADING_SCREEN
commands.short_desc: Forces the whole screen to go black and show the "LOADING..." text on the bottom right corner of the screen. The player is frozen and the game can't be paused while it's on

commands.name: FORCE_WEATHER
commands.short_desc: Activates weather change specified by index

commands.name: FORCE_WEATHER_NOW
commands.short_desc: Activates weather change specified by index

commands.name: GENERATE_RANDOM_FLOAT
commands.short_desc: Returns a random float between the given numbers/floats

commands.name: GENERATE_RANDOM_FLOAT_IN_RANGE
commands.short_desc: Returns a random float between the given numbers/floats

commands.name: GENERATE_RANDOM_INT
commands.short_desc: Returns a random integer between the given integers

commands.name: GENERATE_RANDOM_INT_IN_RANGE
commands.short_desc: Returns a random integer between the given integers

commands.name: GET_ASPECT_RATIO
commands.short_desc: Returns the screen aspect ration. If the aspect ratio is 16:9, then the float returned will be 16 divided by 9, which is 1.778

commands.name: GET_CAR_CHAR_IS_USING
commands.short_desc: Returns the handle of the car driven by the character in P1, and store it to a variable

commands.name: GET_CAR_COLOURS
commands.short_desc: Returns the 1st and the 2nd color ID of the specified vehicle, and store them to variables

commands.name: GET_CAR_COORDINATES
commands.short_desc: Returns the x,y,z coordinates of a car, and store them to variables

commands.name: GET_CAR_MODEL
commands.short_desc: Gets model from a vehicle

commands.name: GET_CHAR_COORDINATES
commands.short_desc: Returns the x,y,z coordinates of the character in P1, and store them to variables

commands.name: GET_CHAR_HEADING
commands.short_desc: Gets the character's heading in degrees

commands.name: GET_CHAR_HEIGHT_ABOVE_GROUND
commands.short_desc: Calculates the Z distance between the specified character and the ground, and return that distance

commands.name: GET_CHAR_VELOCITY
commands.short_desc: Gets x, y and z velocities of the char

commands.name: GET_CLOSEST_CAR
commands.short_desc: Returns the closest car in the specified radius, at the specified coordinates

commands.name: GET_CLOSEST_CAR_NODE
commands.short_desc: Gets the car node closest to the specified position, and stores the position of the node in the variables pointed to by P4, P5 and P6

commands.name: GET_CLOSEST_CAR_NODE_WITH_HEADING
commands.short_desc: Gets the car node closest to the specified position, and stores the position and heading of the node in the variables pointed to by P4, P5, P6 and P7

commands.name: GET_CLOSEST_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Gets the closest character in the specified radius

commands.name: GET_CURRENT_EPISODE
commands.short_desc: Returns an episode number: 0 - Grand Theft Auto 4 (original story), 1 - The Lost And Damned, 2 - The Ballad of Gay Tony

commands.name: GET_CUTSCENE_AUDIO_TIME_MS
commands.short_desc: Returns the current time of audio track, which is used in cutscene

commands.name: GET_CUTSCENE_TIME
commands.short_desc: Returns the total running time of the cutscene

commands.name: GET_DISTANCE_BETWEEN_COORDS_3D
commands.short_desc: Checks distance between x1,y1,z1 and x2,y2,z2 and returns float result in 7 parameter

commands.name: GET_DOOR_ANGLE_RATIO
commands.short_desc: Gets angle of vehicle`s door and store it in parameter 3

commands.name: GET_EPISODE_NAME
commands.short_desc: Returns "BLANK_EPISODE_NAME" in IV, untested in EFLC

commands.name: GET_EXTRA_CAR_COLOURS
commands.short_desc: Returns the 1st and the 2nd specular color ID of the specified vehicle, and store them to variables

commands.name: GET_FLOAT_STAT
commands.short_desc: Returns a value of the float stat

commands.name: GET_GAME_CAM
commands.short_desc: Gets the main game camera which is rotated around player's character with mouse

commands.name: GET_GAME_TIMER
commands.short_desc: Gets time game has been played in milliseconds (time in menu screen does not count)

commands.name: GET_GROUND_Z_FOR_3D_COORD
commands.short_desc: Returns the ground z coordinate of the coordinates in x,y,z and store it to a variable

commands.name: GET_GROUP_SIZE
commands.short_desc: Returns the number of player-controlled and non-player-controlled chars in the specified group. Use GET_PLAYER_GROUP to retrieve the pointer for the current player's group

commands.name: GET_HASH_KEY
commands.short_desc: Calculates a hash key that is required for spawning peds, vehicles, objects, etc

commands.name: GET_HOST_ID
commands.short_desc: Returns the host's ID in a multiplayer lobby

commands.name: GET_INT_STAT
commands.short_desc: Returns a value of the integer stat

commands.name: GET_MODEL_NAME_FOR_DEBUG
commands.short_desc: Returns string "Debug command not in final build" as result

commands.name: GET_MOUSE_POSITION
commands.short_desc: Gets position of game mouse(cursor) and returns it as X and Y coordinates. tracks mouse even if you are not in pause menu

commands.name: GET_MOUSE_WHEEL
commands.short_desc: Gets current mouse wheel status and returns it as integer. Known states: 0=doesn't move; 127=moves up

commands.name: GET_NETWORK_ID_FROM_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Gets object`s network id and store it in parameter 2

commands.name: GET_NETWORK_ID_FROM_PED
commands.short_desc: Gets ped network id and store it in parameter 2

commands.name: GET_NETWORK_ID_FROM_VEHICLE
commands.short_desc: Returns the handle of a car driven by a network player, and store it to a variable. In order to get other network players car handles, you must first use GET_CAR_CHAR_IS_USING

commands.name: GET_NUMBER_OF_CHAR_DRAWABLE_VARIATIONS
commands.short_desc: Gets the number of available drawable variations on the component

commands.name: GET_NUMBER_OF_CHAR_TEXTURE_VARIATIONS
commands.short_desc: Gets all available texture variations in the component and for current drawable variation (GET_CHAR_DRAWABLE_VARIATION)

commands.name: GET_NUMBER_OF_INJURED_PEDS_IN_RANGE
commands.short_desc: Returns you number of injured peds in specified range (p4) and coords (p1,p2,p3)

commands.name: GET_OBJECT_COORDINATES
commands.short_desc: Returns the x,y,z coordinates of the object in Parameter 1, and store them to variables (p2,p3,p4)

commands.name: GET_OBJECT_PED_IS_HOLDING
commands.short_desc: Returns the object the specified ped is holding

commands.name: GET_OFFSET_FROM_CAR_IN_WORLD_COORDS
commands.short_desc: Returns the x,y,z coordinates of the car in P1, with the offsets in P2 P3 and P4, and store them to variables

commands.name: GET_OFFSET_FROM_CHAR_IN_WORLD_COORDS
commands.short_desc: Returns the x,y,z coordinates of the character in P1, with the offsets in P2 P3 and P4, and store them to variables

commands.name: GET_PLAYER_COLOUR
commands.short_desc: Gets the color of specific player and returns it as ID according to the list specified in the description of function: SET_PLAYER_COLOUR

commands.name: GET_PLAYER_GROUP
commands.short_desc: Returns the pointer for the group the player is in

commands.name: GET_PLAYER_ID
commands.short_desc: Returns the Current Player's ID. The Player ID is meaningless for other script functions and should be converted to a Player Index before its used by calling CONVERT_INT_TO_PLAYERINDEX

commands.name: GET_PLAYER_RADIO_STATION_INDEX
commands.short_desc: Returns the index of the current radio station in the player's vehicle

commands.name: GET_PLAYER_RADIO_STATION_NAME
commands.short_desc: Returns the name of the current radio station in the player's vehicle

commands.name: GET_RANDOM_CAR_IN_SPHERE
commands.short_desc: Returns the random car in the specified radius, with the specified hash

commands.name: GET_RANDOM_CAR_IN_SPHERE_NO_SAVE
commands.short_desc: Returns the random car in the specified radius, with the specified hash

commands.name: GET_RANDOM_CHAR_IN_AREA_OFFSET_NO_SAVE
commands.short_desc: Selects a random character in the specified radius and return their pointer in Parameter 7. At the very minimum, GET_RANDOM_CHAR_IN_AREA_OFFSET_NO_SAVE must be preceded by BEGIN_CHAR_SEARCH_CRITERIA and END_CHAR_SEARCH_CRITERIA

commands.name: GET_RID_OF_PLAYER_PROSTITUTE
commands.short_desc: Removes the player's current prostitute. Used before initiating a date

commands.name: GET_SCRIPT_TASK_STATUS
commands.short_desc: Gets the status of a task executed by a script

commands.name: GET_VEHICLE_CLASS
commands.short_desc: Sets the class pointer to -1 (dummy function)

commands.name: GET_VIEWPORT_POS_AND_SIZE
commands.short_desc: Gets the position and size of the specified viewport

commands.name: GET_VIEWPORT_POSITION_OF_COORD
commands.short_desc: Gets 2D viewport position of in-game 3D coordinates

commands.name: GIVE_DELAYED_WEAPON_TO_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Gives a weapon to the specified ped. It works similarly as GIVE_WEAPON_TO_CHAR

commands.name: GIVE_PED_AMBIENT_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Gives an ambient object to the character, and plays proper ambient animations for some of the objects. Model must be loaded before calling this function, or game might crash

commands.name: GIVE_PED_HELMET
commands.short_desc: Gives a helmet to the specified ped

commands.name: GIVE_PED_HELMET_WITH_OPTS
commands.short_desc: Gives a helmet to the specified ped with parameter (P2). If P2 = 0 - ped will drop the helmet after 4-5 seconds. Just like Nico gets out from bike, taking off and drop his helmet. But if P2 = 1, ped will never takes off his helmet

commands.name: GIVE_PLAYER_RAGDOLL_CONTROL
commands.short_desc: Makes the user be able to move Niko while he is in ragdoll mode. Ragdoll modes include being drunk and bailing out of a moving car

commands.name: HAS_CAR_RECORDING_BEEN_LOADED
commands.short_desc: Checks if a RRR path requested with REQUEST CAR RECORDING has been loaded

commands.name: HAS_CHAR_BEEN_DAMAGED_BY_CAR
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the character has been damaged by the specified vehicle

commands.name: HAS_CHAR_BEEN_DAMAGED_BY_WEAPON
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the character has been damaged by the specified weapon

commands.name: HAS_CHAR_GOT_WEAPON
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the character has the specified weapon

commands.name: HAS_MODEL_LOADED
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the model specified by the List of models hashes|model hash has been loaded

commands.name: HAS_OBJECT_COLLIDED_WITH_ANYTHING
commands.short_desc: Checks whether the object has collided with anything. To use this function, the object must be recording collisions. Use SET_OBJECT_RECORDS_COLLISIONS to enable collision recording for an object

commands.name: HAS_PLAYER_DAMAGED_AT_LEAST_ONE_PED
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the player has damaged at least one ped

commands.name: HAVE_ANIMS_LOADED
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating if the specified animation has been loaded.Example Usage:HAVE_ANIMS_LOADED("amb@atm")

commands.name: INIT_CUTSCENE
commands.short_desc: Loads a cutscene with the name

commands.name: IS_BUTTON_JUST_PRESSED
commands.short_desc: Gets if a specified button is pressed or not. Not really sure what the difference is from IS_BUTTON_PRESSED

commands.name: IS_BUTTON_PRESSED
commands.short_desc: Gets if a specified button is pressed or not

commands.name: IS_CAR_DOOR_DAMAGED
commands.short_desc: Returns true if P1 car door is open. Otherwise returns false

commands.name: IS_CHAR_DEAD
commands.short_desc: Checks if the specified character is dead or not

commands.name: IS_CHAR_SITTING_IN_ANY_CAR
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating if the specified character is in vehicle

commands.name: IS_CHAR_TOUCHING_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Returns true if character is touching specified object

commands.name: IS_CHAR_TOUCHING_OBJECT_ON_FOOT
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the character is touching the specified object

commands.name: IS_CHAR_TOUCHING_VEHICLE
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the character is touching specified vehicle

commands.name: IS_CHAR_TRYING_TO_ENTER_A_LOCKED_CAR
commands.short_desc: Returns whether the specified character is currently trying to enter a locked car

commands.name: IS_DEBUG_CAMERA_ON
commands.short_desc: Returns true if ENABLE_DEBUG_CAM was used

commands.name: IS_MINIGAME_IN_PROGRESS
commands.short_desc: Returns true if a minigame is currently in progress. Returns false if no minigame is in progress. Note: using an in-game PC returns true too

commands.name: IS_PED_CLIMBING
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the specified ped is climbing

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_BEING_ARRESTED
commands.short_desc: Returns if the player is being arrested or not

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_CLIMBING
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the player is climbing

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_CONTROL_ON
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating if the specified player is controllable (SET_PLAYER_CONTROL)

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_DEAD
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the player is dead

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_FREE_AIMING_AT_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the character is aiming at the specified ped/character

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_FREE_FOR_AMBIENT_TASK
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the player is free for ambient tasks

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_PRESSING_HORN
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating if the specified player is pressing the cars horn

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_TARGETTING_ANYTHING
commands.short_desc: Returns true only when player lock on target

commands.name: IS_PLAYER_TARGETTING_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the player is targetting a character

commands.name: IS_SCORE_GREATER
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the players score is greater than the specified score

commands.name: IS_USING_CONTROLLER
commands.short_desc: Checks if player is using an XBox 360 controller at the time of the call to this function

commands.name: IS_VEH_WINDOW_INTACT
commands.short_desc: Checks whether the specified vehicle window is intact

commands.name: IS_VEHICLE_EXTRA_TURNED_ON
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the vehicle extra of specified ID is turned on for the specified vehicle

commands.name: IS_VEHICLE_TOUCHING_OBJECT
commands.short_desc: Returns whether the specified vehicle is touching the specified object

commands.name: IS_WANTED_LEVEL_GREATER
commands.short_desc: Returns true if the player's wanted level is greater than the integer value you put in as the second parameter

commands.name: IS_WORLD_POINT_WITHIN_BRAIN_ACTIVATION_RANGE
commands.short_desc: Returns whether the calling script's world point is within its desired range from the player. A World point refers to a position defined in ambient*.ipl

commands.name: KNOCK_PED_OFF_BIKE
commands.short_desc: Knocks ped off of bike. To use this, first check if the vehicle is a bike (using GET_CAR_MODEL and IS_THIS_MODEL_A_BIKE), then check if there is a ped on the bike (using GET_DRIVER_OF_CAR and IS_CAR_PASSENGER_SEAT_FREE)

commands.name: LOCK_CAR_DOORS
commands.short_desc: Sets the lock status of car doors

commands.name: LOCK_LAZLOW_STATION
commands.short_desc: Disables the radio station Integrity 2.0. If the station is being played, the radio will be turned off. The station will not be accessible in the game, neither in a vehicle nor in the pause menu. The station can be enabled using UNLOCK_LAZLOW_STATION

commands.name: M
commands.short_desc: Makes the game delete the vehicle when appropiate (i.e. no player is in proximity). Works with any vehicle, not just cars

commands.name: MARK_CAR_AS_NO_LONGER_NEEDED
commands.short_desc: Makes the game delete the vehicle when appropiate (i.e. no player is in proximity). Works with any vehicle, not just cars

commands.name: MARK_CHAR_AS_NO_LONGER_NEEDED
commands.short_desc: Makes the game delete the character when appropiate (i.e. no player is in proximity) and basically makes them just like any other normal pedestrian, if the character was in a car it will drive off, if not then start walking on the nearest path

commands.name: MARK_MODEL_AS_NO_LONGER_NEEDED
commands.short_desc: Decrements reference counter on the model specified by model hash so that it can be freed when there are no more references to it

commands.name: MUTE_GAMEWORLD_AND_POSITIONED_RADIO_FOR_TV
commands.short_desc: Mutes almost all sounds in the game. Some "front end" sounds, like info beeps and cell phone beeps, car radios, cutscenes, and the TV aren't affected

commands.name: NETWORK_ADVERTISE_SESSION
commands.short_desc: Sets whether the network should be advertised or not

commands.name: NETWORK_GET_GAME_MODE
commands.short_desc: Returns an integer value of the currently running multiplayer game mode. Value is between 0 and 16. If multiplayer is not running, it returns -1

commands.name: NETWORK_SET_PLAYER_MUTED
commands.short_desc: Sets whether or not you can hear the player talking on the mic

commands.name: OPEN_CAR_DOOR
commands.short_desc: Opens a door of the specified vehicle. To close a door call SHUT_CAR_DOOR

commands.name: OPEN_GARAGE
commands.short_desc: Opens the garage door. Basically it used in missions

commands.name: PLAY_AUDIO_EVENT
commands.short_desc: Plays an audio event anywhere

commands.name: POINT_CAM_AT_PED
commands.short_desc: Points a camera(param 1) to PED (param 2). After using you have to upoint camera with UNPOINT_CAM native

commands.name: PREVIEW_RINGTONE
commands.short_desc: Plays the sound for the specified ringtone. To stop the sound played call STOP_PREVIEW_RINGTONE. It functions similarly to START_CUSTOM_MOBILE_PHONE_RINGING

commands.name: PRINT
commands.short_desc: Prints the GTX entry listed in P1, for the amount of time in milliseconds in P2, at the bottom of the screen. This is similar to the TEXT_NOW opcode in the III/VC/SA games

commands.name: PRINT_NOW
commands.short_desc: Prints the GTX entry listed in P1, for the amount of time in milliseconds in P2, at the bottom of the screen. This is similar to the TEXT_NOW opcode in the III/VC/SA games

commands.name: PRINT_STRING_WITH_LITERAL_STRING
commands.short_desc: Prints the string specified in P2, for the amount of time in milliseconds in P3, at the bottom of the screen

commands.name: PRINT_STRING_WITH_LITERAL_STRING_NOW
commands.short_desc: Prints the string specified in P2, for the amount of time in milliseconds in P3, at the bottom of the screen

commands.name: PROCESS_MISSION_DELETION_LIST
commands.short_desc: Starts deletion of peds and cars was added to mission deletion list

commands.name: REMOVE_ALL_CHAR_WEAPONS
commands.short_desc: Removes all the specified characters weapons

commands.name: REMOVE_CAR_WINDOW
commands.short_desc: Removes a window of the specified vehicle

commands.name: REMOVE_CHAR_ELEGANTLY
commands.short_desc: Removes the specified character "elegantly"

commands.name: REMOVE_PTFX_FROM_PED
commands.short_desc: Removes any particle effects from the specified ped

commands.name: REMOVE_PTFX_FROM_VEHICLE
commands.short_desc: Removes any particle effects from the vehicle

commands.name: REQUEST_ANIMS
commands.short_desc: Loads an animation file into memory

commands.name: REQUEST_CAR_RECORDING
commands.short_desc: Loads a RRR path with specified number

commands.name: REQUEST_CONTROL_OF_NETWORK_ID
commands.short_desc: Requests control of a network id

commands.name: REQUEST_MODEL
commands.short_desc: Loads a model specified by the model hash

commands.name: REQUEST_STREAMED_TXD
commands.short_desc: Requests .wtd texture dictionary file which is streamed via server streaming system

commands.name: RETUNE_RADIO_TO_STATION_INDEX
commands.short_desc: Retunes the radio in the player's vehicle to the station with given index

commands.name: RETUNE_RADIO_TO_STATION_NAME
commands.short_desc: Retunes the radio in the player's vehicle to the station with given name. If the player is not in a vehicle already, the radio will be retuned the next time the player is in a vehicle

commands.name: REVIVE_INJURED_PED
commands.short_desc: Revives the specified ped

commands.name: ROUND
commands.short_desc: Rounds the number to a whole integer. If the tenth place is at or above 5, the number will be rounded up to the next whole number (Ceiling). If the tenth digit is 4 (or below), the number will be rounded down to the next whole number (Floor)

commands.name: SAY_AMBIENT_SPEECH
commands.short_desc: Makes the specified character say the specified phrase. If P5 is 1, speech that ends with _MEGAPHONE will be spoken without echo

commands.name: SET_AMBIENT_VOICE_NAME
commands.short_desc: Replaces the character's speech with another character's speech. Other voices like grunts and pains will not be replaced. The majority of available character speeches can be found in the speech.rpf file

commands.name: SET_AMMO_IN_CLIP
commands.short_desc: Sets ammo in the given weapon to the given amount

commands.name: SET_ANIM_GROUP_FOR_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Sets ped animation group, which can be used, for example, to change walking style

commands.name: SET_CAM_ACTIVE
commands.short_desc: Deactivates a specific camera (freezes it) if the second parameter is set to false

commands.name: SET_CAM_BEHIND_PED
commands.short_desc: Sets the camera behind the player

commands.name: SET_CAM_PROPAGATE
commands.short_desc: Switches the main game view to a specific camera. Only one camera can be active at the same time

commands.name: SET_CAMERA_CONTROLS_DISABLED_WITH_PLAYER_CONTROLS
commands.short_desc: Makes the camera controllable if certain functions, commonly SET_PLAYER_CONTROL, would otherwise make the camera uncontrollable

commands.name: SET_CAN_BURST_CAR_TYRES
commands.short_desc: Sets whether the tires of the vehicle can burst. Does nothing for vehicles that don't have tires

commands.name: SET_CAR_AS_MISSION_CAR
commands.short_desc: Marks the specified vehicle so it will not be deleted from game world; opposite of "MARK_CAR_AS_NO_LONGER_NEEDED" function. Vehicle will not be deleted no matter how far player is from it even if vehicle is destroyed. Use "MARK_CAR_AS_NO_LONGER_NEEDED" function to flag the game to dispose of it when appropiate

commands.name: SET_CAR_CAN_BE_DAMAGED
commands.short_desc: Enables the damage counter of the specified vehicle. To enable or disable the visible damage call SET_CAR_CAN_BE_VISIBLY_DAMAGED

commands.name: SET_CAR_CAN_BE_VISIBLY_DAMAGED
commands.short_desc: Enables the visible damage of the specified vehicle. To enable or disable the damage counter call SET CAR CAN BE DAMAGED

commands.name: SET_CAR_COLLISION
commands.short_desc: Enables collision detection for the specified vehicle

commands.name: SET_CAR_ENGINE_ON
commands.short_desc: Turns the vehicles engine on or off, depending on the state put into it

commands.name: SET_CAR_FORWARD_SPEED
commands.short_desc: Sets the car current speed (only forward)

commands.name: SET_CAR_HEADING
commands.short_desc: Sets the rotation of the vehicle

commands.name: SET_CAR_ON_GROUND_PROPERLY
commands.short_desc: Tries to put the vehicle on the ground properly

commands.name: SET_CAR_VISIBLE
commands.short_desc: Sets the specified car visibility

commands.name: SET_CHAR_ACCURACY
commands.short_desc: Sets the character accuracy. Accuracy appears to be from 0 to 100

commands.name: SET_CHAR_AMMO
commands.short_desc: Sets the specified weapons ammo

commands.name: SET_CHAR_AS_ENEMY
commands.short_desc: Sets the specified character as an enemy

commands.name: SET_CHAR_AS_MISSION_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Makes the specified character a mission character. Before you can use any other SET_CHAR_ functions on a character you didn't create, you have to set them as mission chars. It is essentially the opposite of MARK_CHAR_AS_NO_LONGER_NEEDED

commands.name: SET_CHAR_CAN_BE_KNOCKED_OFF_BIKE
commands.short_desc: Prevents a character from being ejected from a motorbike through collisions. Unlike most functions, setting it to 0 means the character can be knocked off the bike and 1 means the player will not be knocked off. seems to affected by SET_CHAR_PROOFS. After is turned on, the function will stay on if the character is collision-proof. Turning off will not work until the collision-proof is turned off

commands.name: SET_CHAR_CANT_BE_DRAGGED_OUT
commands.short_desc: Sets if the character can be dragged out of a vehicle

commands.name: SET_CHAR_COLLISION
commands.short_desc: Enables collision detection for the specified ped

commands.name: SET_CHAR_COORDINATES
commands.short_desc: Warps the character in P1 to the coordinates in x,y, and z. Similar to SET_CHAR_COORDINATES_NO_OFFSET but the character's feet is the point where the character will be placed by

commands.name: SET_CHAR_COORDINATES_NO_OFFSET
commands.short_desc: Warps the character in P1 to the coordinates in x,y, and z. Similar to SET_CHAR_COORDINATES but the character's torso is the point where the character will be placed by

commands.name: SET_CHAR_DROPS_WEAPONS_WHEN_DEAD
commands.short_desc: Makes the character drop their weapons when they die, if set to true

commands.name: SET_CHAR_DRUGGED_UP
commands.short_desc: Sets the character drugged up

commands.name: SET_CHAR_HEADING
commands.short_desc: Turns selected character at certain angle

commands.name: SET_CHAR_HEALTH
commands.short_desc: Sets the characters health to the specified number

commands.name: SET_CHAR_INVINCIBLE
commands.short_desc: Sets the character to invincible, if set to true

commands.name: SET_CHAR_KEEP_TASK
commands.short_desc: Makes the characters task to keep on if true and otherwise if false. Use after every TASK_.... function

commands.name: SET_CHAR_MONEY
commands.short_desc: Sets the specified character's money to the specified amount

commands.name: SET_CHAR_NEVER_LEAVES_GROUP
commands.short_desc: Sets whether the character will leave their group if the character is out of the group separation range (SET_GROUP_SEPARATION_RANGE)

commands.name: SET_CHAR_PROP_INDEX
commands.short_desc: Sets a ped's prop (hats, glasses, etc) variation, similar to component variations

commands.name: SET_CHAR_READY_TO_BE_EXECUTED
commands.short_desc: Makes "crosshair" flash when you targeting this ped (in parameter 1) with pistol

commands.name: SET_CHAR_RELATIONSHIP
commands.short_desc: Assigns the ped specified in Parameter 1 to the relationship group specified in Parameter 2

commands.name: SET_CHAR_RELATIONSHIP_GROUP
commands.short_desc: Assigns the ped specified in Parameter 1 to the relationship group specified in Parameter 2

commands.name: SET_CHAR_SHOOT_RATE
commands.short_desc: Sets the speed the character will shoot. Appears to be from 0 to 100 (100 appears to be a very high rate of fire)

commands.name: SET_CHAR_VELOCITY
commands.short_desc: Sets x, y and z velocities of the char

commands.name: SET_CHAR_VISIBLE
commands.short_desc: Sets the specified characters visibility

commands.name: SET_CHAR_WILL_MOVE_WHEN_INJURED
commands.short_desc: Determines if an injured ped will move in agony. Ped is injured if they are on the ground after being shot, but have not died yet

commands.name: SET_CREATE_RANDOM_COPS
commands.short_desc: Prevents cops from spawning. Already spawned cops will not be removed. If the player has no wanted level, cops on foot and in cars will not spawn. If the player has a wanted level, only cops on foot will not spawn. Cops in cars and helicopters will spawn as usual

commands.name: SET_CURRENT_CHAR_WEAPON
commands.short_desc: Sets the current weapon in the peds hand

commands.name: SET_DRAW_PLAYER_COMPONENT
commands.short_desc: Removes the player's body part from view

commands.name: SET_DRIVE_TASK_CRUISE_SPEED
commands.short_desc: Sets the driving speed for a specified Ped

commands.name: SET_DRUNK_CAM
commands.short_desc: Sets the specified camera to the 'drunken' mode

commands.name: SET_EXTRA_CAR_COLOURS
commands.short_desc: Changes the specular colors of the specified vehicle

commands.name: SET_FAKE_WANTED_LEVEL
commands.short_desc: Sets a fake wanted level. Its effects can only be seen if the player has no wanted level. If the player does have a wanted level, its effects can only be seen after the wanted level is cleared. The radar will show the search zone and the HUD will display the wanted level but the cops will behave as if the player has no wanted level. The search zone will follow the player. To clear the fake wanted level, set the fake wanted level to 0

commands.name: SET_FLOAT_STAT
commands.short_desc: Sets a new value of the float stat

commands.name: SET_FOLLOW_VEHICLE_CAM_OFFSET
commands.short_desc: Changes follow camera offset to specifed offset (p2,p3,p4). But disables camera moving with mouse

commands.name: SET_FOLLOW_VEHICLE_CAM_SUBMODE
commands.short_desc: Sets the camera mode when driving

commands.name: SET_FREE_HEALTH_CARE
commands.short_desc: Lets you be wasted for free. Normally health care costs 10% of the your money up to a maximum of $10,000 when you get wasted

commands.name: SET_GRAVITY_OFF
commands.short_desc: Turns off gravity. Vehicles are not affected by this. Once objects leave the ground, they can float away

commands.name: SET_GROUP_CHAR_DUCKS_WHEN_AIMED_AT
commands.short_desc: Makes the specified group member duck when player (of same group) aims at them

commands.name: SET_GROUP_FORMATION
commands.short_desc: Sets the the group formation to the type specified

commands.name: SET_GROUP_FORMATION_SPACING
commands.short_desc: Sets the spacing, in meters, for the npc members of a group

commands.name: SET_GROUP_LEADER
commands.short_desc: Sets the specified character as the leader of the specified group

commands.name: SET_GROUP_MEMBER
commands.short_desc: Adds the ped specified in the second parameter to the group specified in the first parameter

commands.name: SET_GROUP_SEPARATION_RANGE
commands.short_desc: Makes a member, at least an npc, of the specified group appear to leave the group if this "Distance" between the member and their group is exceeded

commands.name: SET_HELI_BLADES_FULL_SPEED
commands.short_desc: Sets the rotors of the helicopter to full speed. Nothing happens if the vehicle is not a helicopter

commands.name: SET_HELI_STABILISER
commands.short_desc: Stabilizes the helicopter. Nothing happens if the vehicle is not a helicopter

commands.name: SET_INSTANT_WIDESCREEN_BORDERS
commands.short_desc: Removes the HUD and radar. It doesn't seem to do anymore than this

commands.name: SET_INT_STAT
commands.short_desc: Sets a new value of the integer stat

commands.name: SET_MAX_WANTED_LEVEL
commands.short_desc: Sets the max stars you can get for your wanted level. It will not clear your current wanted level

commands.name: SET_MESSAGES_WAITING
commands.short_desc: Sets a waiting text message notification to show on the bottom left corner of the radar

commands.name: SET_NETWORK_ID_CAN_MIGRATE
commands.short_desc: Allows network id to migrate from server to client and conversely (with REQUEST_CONTROL_OF_NETWORK_ID and RETURN_CONTROL_OF_NETWORK_ID_TO_SERVER for example)

commands.name: SET_NEXT_DESIRED_MOVE_STATE
commands.short_desc: Sets the move state when actor enters in vehicle (as usually in original .sco)

commands.name: SET_NO_RESPRAYS
commands.short_desc: Sets the activity of spray shops. When is on, the doors of spray shops will not open. If it is already opened, the spray shop will not respray the car. When is off, spray shops become active. If the doors of spray shops are closed, it will open itself. Do not turn on while the car is being resprayed

commands.name: SET_OBJECT_ALPHA
commands.short_desc: Sets object's alpha. 0 is fully invisible, 255 is fully visible

commands.name: SET_OBJECT_AS_STEALABLE
commands.short_desc: Allows picking up and throwing this object

commands.name: SET_OBJECT_LIGHTS
commands.short_desc: Sets the light of the object

commands.name: SET_OBJECT_RECORDS_COLLISIONS
commands.short_desc: Makes the object record collisions

commands.name: SET_OBJECT_VISIBLE
commands.short_desc: Sets the visibility of the object

commands.name: SET_PED_DENSITY_MULTIPLIER
commands.short_desc: Adjusts the ped density like 03DE in vc

commands.name: SET_PED_IS_DRUNK
commands.short_desc: Makes the specified ped drunk or not drunk

commands.name: SET_PED_PATH_MAY_DROP_FROM_HEIGHT
commands.short_desc: Allows an NPC to jump off of, possibly low, heights. If an NPC is on top of a building, not a tall one, they will jump off to land on ground if they need to

commands.name: SET_PED_PATH_MAY_USE_CLIMBOVERS
commands.short_desc: Allows an NPC to climb over walls and whatever else can be climbed

commands.name: SET_PED_PATH_MAY_USE_LADDERS
commands.short_desc: Allows an NPC to use ladders

commands.name: SET_PHONE_HUD_ITEM
commands.short_desc: Creates a cell phone notification seen above the radar

commands.name: SET_PLAYER_COLOUR
commands.short_desc: Sets color of specific player in multiplayer. affects on displayed color of name and circle above player's head. Works only on client side.NOTE: Player colors and blip colors are not the same and have different color IDs

commands.name: SET_PLAYER_CONTROL
commands.short_desc: Toggles if the specified player is controllable

commands.name: SET_PLAYER_KEEPS_WEAPONS_WHEN_RESPAWNED
commands.short_desc: Sets if the player keeps his weapons after dying and respawning

commands.name: SET_PLAYER_MAY_ONLY_ENTER_THIS_VEHICLE
commands.short_desc: Limits the specified player to only be able to enter a specific vehicle. This changes the behaviour of the "Enter Vehicle" key to always enter the specified vehicle. Regardless of distance

commands.name: SET_RELATIONSHIP
commands.short_desc: Sets the group in Parameter 2 to have the relationship type specified in Parameter 1 with the group in Parameter 3.For instance, the parameters (5, 14, 15) would make the MEDIC group (14) hate (5) the FIREMEN group (15)

commands.name: SET_ROMANS_MOOD
commands.short_desc: Sets the mood of Roman. Roman has four sets of audio that can be chosen with this function.*0 = normal*1 = sad*2 = shaken up*3 = drunkAny higher values will use Roman's normal audio. This can be called at any time, even after Roman is spawned

commands.name: SET_ROUTE
commands.short_desc: Draws the path on the map and radar to a specified blip (like for a waypoint). Color of the route depends on color of blip

commands.name: SET_SENSE_RANGE
commands.short_desc: Sets the distance in which the character will be alert to enemies.NOTE: Uncertain on its effects on player controlled chars and if anymore effects exist (i.e. blips showing up or not on radar)

commands.name: SET_STATE_OF_CLOSEST_DOOR_OF_TYPE
commands.short_desc: Appears to locks/unlocks doors to interior buildings

commands.name: SET_TAXI_LIGHTS
commands.short_desc: Sets the taxi light state (on/off)

commands.name: SET_TEXT_FONT
commands.short_desc: Sets the font to be used

commands.name: SET_TIME_OF_DAY
commands.short_desc: Sets time of the game

commands.name: SET_TIME_SCALE
commands.short_desc: Sets the overall gamespeed. The default value is 1.0. Half the gamespeed would be 0.5

commands.name: SET_USE_HIGHDOF
commands.short_desc: Sets the use of high "depth of vision." It only works when the blur filter is on and has no effect when it's off. It mainly creates more blur to mid-distance objects

commands.name: SET_VEH_ALARM
commands.short_desc: Marks the specified vehicle to have or not the alarm activated. Deactivating the alarm, also stops any alarm sound and hazard lights. Activating the alarm does not produce any sound or visual effect.Only tested this on a locked car

commands.name: SET_VEH_HAZARDLIGHTS
commands.short_desc: Turns on or off the hazard lights of the specified vehicle

commands.name: SET_VEH_INDICATORLIGHTS
commands.short_desc: Turns on or off all the indicator lights of a specified vehicle

commands.name: SET_VEH_INTERIORLIGHT
commands.short_desc: Turns on or off the interior light of the specified vehicle

commands.name: SET_VEHICLE_DIRT_LEVEL
commands.short_desc: Changes the dirt level of the specified vehicle. You can exceed the maximum and briefly see the change but the game will prevent the car from being dirtier than the maximum. To clean the vehicle, set the level to 0.0 or call WASH_VEHICLE_TEXTURES with 255 in 2nd parameter

commands.name: SHOW_SIGNIN_UI
commands.short_desc: Opens the Xbox 360 Guide asking you to select a profile

commands.name: SHUT_CAR_DOOR
commands.short_desc: Closes a door of the specified vehicle. To open a door call OPEN CAR DOOR

commands.name: SMASH_CAR_WINDOW
commands.short_desc: Smashes the specified window

commands.name: SOUND_CAR_HORN
commands.short_desc: Sounds the car horn for the specified amount of milliseconds.If the vehicle has no driver, nothing will happen

commands.name: START_CAR_FIRE
commands.short_desc: Starts specified vehicle on fire

commands.name: START_CHAR_FIRE
commands.short_desc: Starts specified character on fire

commands.name: START_CUSTOM_MOBILE_PHONE_RINGING
commands.short_desc: Starts the ringing of a cell phone. It will keep ringing until STOP_MOBILE_PHONE_RINGING is used to stop it

commands.name: START_PTFX
commands.short_desc: Starts a particle effect at the specified location with the specified rotation

commands.name: START_PTFX_ON_OBJ
commands.short_desc: Starts and sticks a particle effect to an object. (effect follows object around)

commands.name: START_PTFX_ON_PED
commands.short_desc: Starts and sticks a particle effect to a ped. (effect follows ped around)

commands.name: START_PTFX_ON_PED_BONE
commands.short_desc: Starts and sticks a particle effect to a ped's bone. Returns a handle to the ptfx instance

commands.name: START_PTFX_ON_VEH
commands.short_desc: Starts and sticks a particle effect to a vehicle. (effect follows vehicle around). Returns a handle to the ptfx instance

commands.name: STOP_PREVIEW_RINGTONE
commands.short_desc: Stops the sound of the ringtone started with PREVIEW_RINGTONE

commands.name: STOP_PTFX
commands.short_desc: Stops the specified particle effect instance

commands.name: STORE_CAR_CHAR_IS_IN
commands.short_desc: Returns the handle of the car where the character is

commands.name: STORE_CAR_CHAR_IS_IN_NO_SAVE
commands.short_desc: Returns the handle of the car where the character is

commands.name: STRING_TO_INT
commands.short_desc: Converts a given string to an integer number and store the result to a variable. If the function fails (a string could not be converted to an integer number) the result is false, otherwise true. If the first parameter is NULL, the function returns false and the variable contains value of -999

commands.name: SWITCH_AMBIENT_PLANES
commands.short_desc: Removes all ambient planes, which are the ones moving in the airport and flying in the air

commands.name: SWITCH_CAR_SIREN
commands.short_desc: Toggles a vehicle's sirens on or off. Only works on vehicle models that support sirens e.g. emergency service vehicles

commands.name: SWITCH_ROADS_OFF
commands.short_desc: Prevents civilian-driven vehicles, including cars and boats, to spawn within the zone. Vehicles spawned outside the area will not travel into the area. Police cars don't spawn in the zone unless the player has a wanted level. Parked vehicles still spawn and mission vehicles still travel into the zone. can be undone using SWITCH_ROADS_BACK_TO_ORIGINAL with the same coordinates used for this function

commands.name: TASK_CAR_MISSION
commands.short_desc: Makes the character use the vehicle to follow the target vehicle The character will get in the driver of the vehicle automatically

commands.name: TASK_CAR_MISSION_PED_TARGET
commands.short_desc: Makes the character use the vehicle to follow the target char. The character will get in the driver of the vehicle automatically

commands.name: TASK_CAR_TEMP_ACTION
commands.short_desc: Assigns a temporary task to a vehicle

commands.name: TASK_CHAR_SLIDE_TO_COORD
commands.short_desc: Makes the character slide to the given coordinates. The character will walk to the approximate coordinate, then slide to the exact coordinate

commands.name: TASK_COMBAT
commands.short_desc: Forces the aggressor (ped from parameter 1) to attack the target (ped from param. 2)

commands.name: TASK_COMBAT_HATED_TARGETS_AROUND_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Makes the character attack any enemies to it, or to the group it is in, who are within the radius of the char. character will continue to follow group leader, though will move slower while firing

commands.name: TASK_DIE
commands.short_desc: Forces the specified character to die

commands.name: TASK_ENTER_CAR_AS_PASSENGER
commands.short_desc: Makes the character enter the vehicle as a passenger at the specified seat index. If the character is still trying to get into the vehicle and the "duration" is up, the character will be warped into the vehicle at to seat index.Works on the player character also

commands.name: TASK_EVERYONE_LEAVE_CAR
commands.short_desc: Makes everyone to leave the vehicle

commands.name: TASK_GO_STRAIGHT_TO_COORD
commands.short_desc: Makes the specified character go to the specified coordinates, using the specified move type. If P6 is not -1, the character will warp to the specified coordinates after 2 seconds

commands.name: TASK_GO_TO_COORD_WHILE_AIMING
commands.short_desc: Makes the specified character go to the specified coordinates, using the specified move type, while aiming at the specified aiming coordinates.If P8 is 2, the character will aim at the character specified in P12; Otherwise, it will aim at the target coordinate given in P9, P10 and P11. Use 0 for unknown parameters

commands.name: TASK_GUARD_ASSIGNED_DEFENSIVE_AREA
commands.short_desc: Makes the character guard the specified position for the specified duration

commands.name: TASK_GUARD_CURRENT_POSITION
commands.short_desc: Makes the character guard their current position for the specified duration

commands.name: TASK_LOOK_AT_CHAR
commands.short_desc: Makes character 1 to look at character 2 for the given duration

commands.name: TASK_PLAY_ANIM
commands.short_desc: Makes the character play an animation

commands.name: TASK_PLAY_ANIM_NON_INTERRUPTABLE
commands.short_desc: Makes the ped play anim with no interrupt and disables the player control till the anim will end. In NET play - seen for everybody

commands.name: TASK_SHUFFLE_TO_NEXT_CAR_SEAT
commands.short_desc: Makes the character slide over to the adjacent seat. A character will be kicked out of the vehicle if they are in the seat

commands.name: TASK_SIT_DOWN
commands.short_desc: Makes handled ped (P1) sit down right now. Ped will get up automaticly after time (p4) is up

commands.name: TASK_SIT_DOWN_INSTANTLY
commands.short_desc: Makes handled ped (P1) sit down right now. Ped will get up automaticly after time (p4) is up

commands.name: TASK_SIT_DOWN_ON_SEAT
commands.short_desc: Makes ped sit on seat place (on world point p4 (x), p5 (y), p6 (z)) with specific facing angle (p7) and ped`s own 'seat animation' which can be changed with CHANGE_CHAR_SIT_IDLE_ANIM

commands.name: TERMINATE_ALL_SCRIPTS_WITH_THIS_NAME
commands.short_desc: Ends the script with the name

commands.name: TO_FLOAT
commands.short_desc: Converts the integer value to a floating-point number

commands.name: TRIGGER_MISSION_COMPLETE_AUDIO
commands.short_desc: Plays a mission complete audio usually heard when a mission is completed. The audio are located in the gps.rfp file. Valid values include 6-7, 10-11, 15, 18, 24-25, 27-28, 33-35, 42-43, 50-69, 71. Using other numbers will not play any audio. The audio will only play if a mission complete audio is not currently playing

commands.name: TRIGGER_POLICE_REPORT
commands.short_desc: Plays a police report audio usually played after certain missions are completed or after certain events happened. The audio are located in SCRIPTED_LINES.ivaud in the POLICE_SCANNER.rpf file

commands.name: TRIGGER_VIGILANTE_CRIME
commands.short_desc: Triggers a random police speech reporting a problem at the speccified location. No police arrives, as far as I can tell

commands.name: TURN_OFF_VEHICLE_EXTRA
commands.short_desc: Enables the vehicle extra of the specified id for the specified vehicle. NOTE: Use false to turn ON and true to turn OFF the extra

commands.name: UNLOCK_RAGDOLL
commands.short_desc: Turns off ragdoll for the character. When ragdoll is turned off, movements that relies on ragdoll animations will use prerecorded animations in a way similar to previous games. If the animation doesn't exist, awkward or no movement happens

commands.name: UNPOINT_CAM
commands.short_desc: Unpoints pointed camera (for example with POINT_CAM_AT_PED)

commands.name: UPDATE_PTFX_OFFSETS
commands.short_desc: Updates PTFX offset. Works for all created PTFX

commands.name: VEHICLE_CAN_BE_TARGETTED_BY_HS_MISSILE
commands.short_desc: Returns a boolean indicating whether the specified vehicle can be targetted and followed by a heat seeking missile

commands.name: WAIT
commands.short_desc: Stops an execution of the script for the specified amount of time, similar to opcode 0001 from the GTA III series

commands.name: WARP_CHAR_INTO_CAR
commands.short_desc: Teleports the specified character in the specified vehicle as driver

commands.name: WARP_CHAR_INTO_CAR_AS_PASSENGER
commands.short_desc: Teleports the specified character in the specified vehicle as passenger

commands.name: WAS_CUTSCENE_SKIPPED
commands.short_desc: Checks whether the missing cutscene

commands.name: WASH_VEHICLE_TEXTURES
commands.short_desc: Removes the dirt on the texture of the specified vehicle

commands.name: SET_PED_FORCE_FLY_THROUGH_WINDSCREEN
commands.short_desc: Forces the specified character out the windscreen

commands.name: GET_VEHICLE_ENGINE_REVS
commands.short_desc: Gets the engine revs

commands.name: GET_VEHICLE_GEAR
commands.short_desc: Gets the current vehicle gear and returns it as a number from 1 to 5 if the car moves forward, or false if it moves backward

commands.name: REMOVE_PTFX
commands.short_desc: Removes any particle effects from the specified ped

classes.name: Player
classes.desc: The Main Character Controlled by a Player
